Esther Matumane was travelling with her two children and a male passenger when they came under attack on Wednesday. JOHANNESBURG - Police are searching for a suspect or suspects responsible for the murder of an African National Congress (ANC) councillor in Pretoria. Esther Matumane was travelling with her two children and a male passenger when they came under attack on Wednesday. Matumane died in hospital and the passenger was wounded, while the children escaped unharmed. (Edited by Mihlali Ntsabo)